15:37.166 --> 15:39.867
6 billion
and counting.

15:39.934 --> 15:43.467
Suddenly, my cell
don't seem so cramped.

15:44.800 --> 15:46.500
- I don't know how
I'm gonna give Julie up.

15:46.567 --> 15:48.000
Huh?

15:48.066 --> 15:49.967
I had a kid once,

15:50.033 --> 15:51.734
died.

15:51.800 --> 15:54.533
It fuckin'
nearly crippled me.

15:54.600 --> 15:58.367
I ain't felt love
since then...

15:58.433 --> 15:59.834
until now.

16:00.767 --> 16:03.033
- You know that CO
that you blinded?

16:03.100 --> 16:04.233
- Eugene Rivera?

16:04.300 --> 16:05.533
- Yeah, is he gonna
get your dog?

16:05.600 --> 16:06.734
- Well...

16:06.800 --> 16:08.467
He said he don't
want any part of anything

16:08.533 --> 16:10.767
that had
to do with me.

16:10.834 --> 16:13.900
- Have you ever seen these
babies fight for sport?

16:14.967 --> 16:15.934
- I've seen roosters.

16:16.000 --> 16:17.633
I haven't
seen dogs, though.

16:17.700 --> 16:19.467
- It's fuckin' brutal,
man.

16:19.533 --> 16:22.266
Three rounds of
absolute mayhem.

16:22.333 --> 16:24.300
Dogs are just rippin'
each other apart.

16:24.367 --> 16:26.300
- Jesus Christ,
fuckin' stop!

16:26.367 --> 16:28.300
I'm sorry.

16:36.567 --> 16:38.200
- Hey, Penders,
Alvarez,

16:38.266 --> 16:39.734
what's this?

16:41.900 --> 16:43.333
- Beats me.

16:43.400 --> 16:45.500
- It's dog shit,
dickhead.

16:45.567 --> 16:48.734
- How can you be sure
that a dog did that?

16:48.800 --> 16:51.100
- Who else shits
on the floor?

16:51.166 --> 16:52.934
- Guerra.

16:53.000 --> 16:54.066
- That's funny.

16:54.133 --> 16:55.066
Clean it up.

16:55.133 --> 16:56.266
- No.

16:56.333 --> 16:57.600
- No?
- No.

16:57.667 --> 17:00.667
- Clean the fuckin'
shit up.

17:00.734 --> 17:03.033
- Lopresti, why you always
on my fuckin' ass?

17:03.100 --> 17:06.033
- Because I'm tired of you
and your fuckin' pooch.

17:06.100 --> 17:07.867
- At least Chester
doesn't have bad breath.

17:12.433 --> 17:13.633
men: Ohh!

17:13.700 --> 17:15.500
- Shit.

17:17.767 --> 17:19.033
- Chester, now,
Chester!

17:29.633 --> 17:32.133
- Yes. Yes, Chester.

17:32.200 --> 17:33.233
- Damn!

17:37.300 --> 17:38.567
- It's a shame
what Penders did,

17:38.633 --> 17:40.033
teaching Chester
to attack.

17:41.100 --> 17:42.934
He put a shadow
over the whole program.

17:43.000 --> 17:45.633
- Yeah, you know,
he really loved the dog.

17:45.700 --> 17:48.000
He just
fuckin' hates people.

17:48.066 --> 17:50.000
- Let her take you
up the stairs.

17:57.800 --> 17:58.734
- What else?

17:58.800 --> 18:00.100
- Have her sit.

18:00.166 --> 18:02.567
- Julie, sit.

18:04.400 --> 18:06.433
Good girl, and?

18:06.500 --> 18:08.900
- Now take off
your blindfold.

18:11.767 --> 18:12.867
- I pass?

18:12.934 --> 18:14.767
- Yes, A+,

18:14.834 --> 18:17.300
gold star,
great job.

18:17.367 --> 18:20.100
- Thanks, she did
all the work, you know?

18:20.166 --> 18:23.734
- And she'll continue
to do so, thanks to you.

18:25.834 --> 18:28.567
- You know what I wish?

18:28.633 --> 18:30.033
I wish I could
just see

18:30.100 --> 18:31.533
whoever's gonna
get her, you know?

18:31.600 --> 18:34.133
- Well, Miguel...

18:34.200 --> 18:36.834
You're gonna
get your wish,

18:36.900 --> 18:39.300
because that person is gonna
be here in just a second.

18:39.367 --> 18:40.867
- Who's that?

18:40.934 --> 18:43.900
- McManus has been working
the phones all morning, and--

18:46.066 --> 18:47.867
- Oh, shit.

18:47.934 --> 18:49.700
I thought
he didn't want her.

18:49.767 --> 18:52.000
- Tina didn't.

18:52.066 --> 18:54.467
Well, neither did I
at first.

18:55.900 --> 18:59.066
Look, I love my wife

18:59.133 --> 19:01.734
and everything
she's done for me,

19:01.800 --> 19:03.633
but she deserves
her life back.

19:03.700 --> 19:07.734
I mean, I know this dog
would be great for me,

19:07.800 --> 19:10.133
but I think...

19:10.200 --> 19:12.633
Over time it would
be great for her too.

19:12.700 --> 19:13.800
- That's good.

19:13.867 --> 19:15.800
Cool.

19:15.867 --> 19:18.166
This is Julie,

19:18.233 --> 19:20.000
and I trained her
special for you, man.

19:20.066 --> 19:21.934
- Special?

19:22.000 --> 19:23.967
- What do you normally
speak at home?

19:24.033 --> 19:25.567
- Spanish.

19:25.633 --> 19:28.100
- Now make believe
you're at home right now

19:28.166 --> 19:29.200
and ask for her.

19:29.266 --> 19:30.900
- Julie?

19:30.967 --> 19:32.734
Ven aca.

19:36.066 --> 19:37.800
- You taught the dog
Spanish?

19:37.867 --> 19:39.200
- Yeah, yeah.

19:39.266 --> 19:42.700
Every command,
she's fuckin' bilingual.

19:42.767 --> 19:45.433
Tell her to sit down.

19:45.500 --> 19:46.967
- Julie...

19:47.033 --> 19:49.000
Sientate.

19:56.000 --> 19:58.033
- She's all yours.

20:02.600 --> 20:04.834
Te voy a echar de manos.

20:11.000 --> 20:14.066
- Come on,
I'll drive you home.

20:15.300 --> 20:16.667
- Let's go.

20:25.633 --> 20:27.500
- Well, congratulations, Tim,
you're two for two.

20:27.567 --> 20:30.266
Both the music program
and the man's best friend

20:30.333 --> 20:32.467
has had tangible
and positive results.

20:32.533 --> 20:33.567
- Hear, hear!

20:33.633 --> 20:34.767
- Thank you.

20:34.834 --> 20:36.033
You know, I just want
to tell you both

20:36.100 --> 20:37.367
that I appreciate
your support,

20:37.433 --> 20:40.066
as guarded and as
half-ass as it's been.

20:40.133 --> 20:41.800
- Ouch.

20:41.867 --> 20:44.800
I was wondering what happened
to that backhand of yours.

20:46.000 --> 20:47.834
Oh, I gotta go.

20:47.900 --> 20:49.567
I'm due over
at Lardner.

20:49.633 --> 20:52.000
Leo, Timmy.

20:56.433 --> 20:57.867
- Well...

20:57.934 --> 21:00.166
There certainly has been
a thaw in your icy relationship

21:00.233 --> 21:01.567
with the governor's office.

21:01.633 --> 21:02.734
- Huh?

21:02.800 --> 21:04.133
- If I didn't know better,

21:04.200 --> 21:06.533
I'd say you had a liaison
with the state liaison,

21:06.600 --> 21:08.800
if not last night,
then very recently.

21:08.867 --> 21:11.200
- Yeah, I gotta go too.

21:11.266 --> 21:13.100
- Okay, Timmy.

21:17.967 --> 21:19.867
- 51.

21:20.667 --> 21:24.133
- Yeah, Jesus Christ,
I fucking won!

21:24.200 --> 21:27.033
- That winning
ticket was mine, damn it!

21:27.100 --> 21:28.467
Have I got
any legal recourse?

21:28.533 --> 21:29.533
- No, no.

21:29.600 --> 21:30.900
I mean, even if
we could find him,

21:30.967 --> 21:33.433
it's Dave Brass' word
against yours.

21:33.500 --> 21:36.200
I mean, he's a CO injured
in the line of duty,

21:36.266 --> 21:38.867
you, a prisoner,
known to talk to God.

21:38.934 --> 21:41.533
- That bastard!

21:41.600 --> 21:43.834
He should be arrested
for killing my grandson.

21:43.900 --> 21:47.266
- Alex Jr.'s only chance to beat
the leukemia is to find a donor,

21:47.333 --> 21:48.967
someone willing
to give his bone marrow.

21:49.033 --> 21:50.233
- I know.

21:50.300 --> 21:52.700
But I thought because of
his unique ethnic mix,

21:52.767 --> 21:54.066
a match was difficult.

21:54.133 --> 21:56.333
- The difficulty is
that no one is looking.

21:56.400 --> 21:57.967
There must be
someone out there.

21:58.033 --> 21:59.300
- Or here.

21:59.367 --> 22:00.800
I'll bet if you
search the computer files

22:00.867 --> 22:02.867
of every prisoner in Oz,
past or present,

22:02.934 --> 22:05.734
you'd get a match.

22:05.800 --> 22:06.734
- Well, why don't I?

22:06.800 --> 22:08.000
- What?

22:08.066 --> 22:10.567
- Search the files.

22:10.633 --> 22:11.867
- You'd do that for me?

22:11.934 --> 22:12.967
- For you,

22:13.033 --> 22:14.533
for your grandson,

22:14.600 --> 22:15.633
for Dave Brass,

22:15.700 --> 22:16.967
for my own
peace of mind.

22:21.066 --> 22:23.667
- Martinez.

22:23.734 --> 22:25.633
I hear they're shipping your ass
back to solitary.

22:25.700 --> 22:26.800
- Yeah.

22:26.867 --> 22:30.300
- Listen, I could
help you out.

22:30.367 --> 22:32.800
A word from me
and you're sitting in Unit B,

22:32.867 --> 22:34.367
maybe even
Emerald City.

22:34.433 --> 22:35.667
- Yeah?

22:35.734 --> 22:37.567
And why would
you help me?

22:39.300 --> 22:42.066
- You douced Dave Brass
for no apparent reason.

22:42.133 --> 22:44.867
Only I'm thinking
you had a reason,

22:44.934 --> 22:47.400
and I'm thinking
if you tell me,

22:47.467 --> 22:50.000
that's maybe when
I can step up for you.

22:52.133 --> 22:54.834
- I got nothing to say.

22:54.900 --> 22:56.500
- You attacked a CO,
Carlos.

22:56.567 --> 22:58.734
Where you're going,
you've got no friends.

22:58.800 --> 23:01.667
- If you don't get smart,

23:01.734 --> 23:05.233
you're gonna fuckin' hurt
a lot more than you do now.

23:12.233 --> 23:14.333
Martinez is cracking.

23:14.400 --> 23:15.867
We're so close to him
jabbering all the names

23:15.934 --> 23:17.900
of everybody involved.

23:17.967 --> 23:20.934
And my guess is
Enrique Morales tops the list.

23:21.000 --> 23:23.066
- Yeah, good, none of that's
gonna do much good

23:23.133 --> 23:24.767
for Rebadow,
though.

23:24.834 --> 23:26.967
I mean, even if we find Brass
and tell him who cut him,

23:27.033 --> 23:29.900
he's not going to give
that lottery money back.

23:31.734 --> 23:34.367
Yes.

23:34.433 --> 23:35.734
Yes, yes.

23:35.800 --> 23:36.734
Got it.

23:36.800 --> 23:37.734
- Got what?

23:37.800 --> 23:39.900
- Salvation.

23:43.266 --> 23:46.300
Farai Gyrobile is
a Rastafarian from Unit C.

23:46.367 --> 23:47.934
Now, it turns out
that him and Bob Marley

23:48.000 --> 23:49.734
have more in common
than just reggae.

23:49.800 --> 23:51.467
Both of them
have white fathers.

23:51.533 --> 23:53.667
- And was his mother
half West Indian,

23:53.734 --> 23:54.667
half Guatemalan?

23:54.734 --> 23:55.967
- Yeah, so he appears to be

23:56.033 --> 23:57.533
the perfect match
for your grandson.

23:57.600 --> 24:00.400
Now all you've gotta do
is convince him

24:00.467 --> 24:01.734
to be the bone marrow
donor.

24:01.800 --> 24:04.800
- May I talk
to this man alone,

24:04.867 --> 24:07.233
prisoner to prisoner?

24:07.300 --> 24:08.333
- Of course.

24:10.800 --> 24:11.867
Good luck.

24:16.700 --> 24:20.633
- Farai,
Bob.

24:20.700 --> 24:21.934
Bob Rebadow.

24:22.000 --> 24:23.233
- The guy who got aced

24:23.300 --> 24:25.166
out of the 2 million
Mightyball dollars.

24:25.233 --> 24:27.333
- Yes, you see...

24:27.400 --> 24:29.500
I needed to win that money
on account of my grandson.

24:29.567 --> 24:32.567
He's dying
of leukemia.

24:32.633 --> 24:34.700
- Pity.

24:34.767 --> 24:37.533
- Which is why
I need your help.

24:37.600 --> 24:39.433
Alex has a...

24:39.500 --> 24:43.667
Very specific racial makeup
which you match exactly.

24:43.734 --> 24:45.767
- How the fuck you know
what makes me up?

24:45.834 --> 24:47.166
- McManus told me.

24:47.233 --> 24:49.767
And I was hoping
you might be willing

24:49.834 --> 24:52.400
to donate your bone marrow
to my grandson.

24:52.467 --> 24:56.233
- McManus has no right
sharing that shit with you!

24:56.300 --> 24:59.300
Everyone here thinks my blood
be black, 100%.

24:59.367 --> 25:00.834
I fuckin' donate,

25:00.900 --> 25:03.066
and they all
know different.

25:03.133 --> 25:05.800
And if you tell a soul,

25:05.867 --> 25:07.934
you're as dead
as your grandboy.

25:09.333 --> 25:11.333
- No, wait.

25:22.166 --> 25:24.100
- I'm sorry, Alex.

25:24.166 --> 25:26.333
I tried.

25:39.300 --> 25:41.667
God spoke to me
last night.

25:41.734 --> 25:43.600
- He told me that
the missing element

25:43.667 --> 25:47.567
in Alex Jr.'s recovery
is faith.

25:47.633 --> 25:49.867
- Uh-huh.

25:49.934 --> 25:51.834
- Not money,
not science.

25:51.900 --> 25:53.633
I want to find
a faith healer,

25:53.700 --> 25:56.433
someone who will go
to my grandson in the hospital,

25:56.500 --> 25:58.000
lay hands on him,

25:58.066 --> 26:00.567
flush out the leukemia
once and for all.

26:00.633 --> 26:03.100
- I see.

26:03.166 --> 26:04.834
- You're wary.

26:04.900 --> 26:06.900
- What little I do know
of faith healers

26:06.967 --> 26:08.700
gives me pause.

26:08.767 --> 26:11.133
A lot of people
expecting a miracle...

26:11.200 --> 26:13.700
get deception instead.

26:13.767 --> 26:15.133
- Okay.

26:15.200 --> 26:17.367
So you don't
choose the bruised fruit.

26:17.433 --> 26:18.967
You look carefully.

26:19.033 --> 26:20.300
- For whatever
it's worth,

26:20.367 --> 26:21.867
the kind of people
you're talking about

26:21.934 --> 26:25.667
are not typically
sanctioned by any church.

26:25.734 --> 26:27.667
- Sister Pete,

26:27.734 --> 26:29.367
I didn't say
religious healer,

26:29.433 --> 26:31.100
denominational healer.

26:31.166 --> 26:33.767
I said faith healer,
the faith that

26:33.834 --> 26:36.767
alone transcends all
cultural divisions and systems.

26:36.834 --> 26:38.500
Aren't you sick of
the club mentality

26:38.567 --> 26:41.033
surrounded by members
of other clubs,

26:41.100 --> 26:43.200
who belongs to what

26:43.266 --> 26:45.934
and which one
has the upper hand on God?

26:47.433 --> 26:49.834
I mean no offense,
but I don't want to belong.

26:49.900 --> 26:51.300
I just want
to believe.

26:51.367 --> 26:53.900
- So what happens next?

26:53.967 --> 26:55.633
- I wait for
instructions.

26:55.700 --> 26:58.533
I wait for the word.

26:58.600 --> 27:00.900
I am an arrow
in God's bow.

27:18.533 --> 27:20.333
- How long has he got?

27:20.400 --> 27:21.934
- What?

27:23.233 --> 27:25.266
- Your grandson,

27:25.333 --> 27:26.900
how long has he got?

27:26.967 --> 27:28.233
- Who are you?

27:28.300 --> 27:30.233
- A.R. Whitworth.

27:30.300 --> 27:32.767
How long has he got?

27:32.834 --> 27:34.600
- I don't know,
only God does.

27:34.667 --> 27:37.033
- Good answer.

27:37.100 --> 27:38.300
Now we're talking.

27:38.367 --> 27:39.967
- About what?

27:40.033 --> 27:44.066
- Faith healing,
right?

27:44.133 --> 27:46.233
- How do you know that?

27:46.300 --> 27:47.900
- Would you believe
that last night

27:47.967 --> 27:52.467
I dreamt that your grandson
was restored to perfect health?

27:52.533 --> 27:54.967
- Maybe.

27:55.033 --> 27:59.000
- Go on.
- All right.

27:59.066 --> 28:00.533
I was born a gimp,

28:00.600 --> 28:05.066
spinal shit,
impossible to fix.

28:05.133 --> 28:06.467
When I was
in high school,

28:06.533 --> 28:09.033
found out that my neighbor's
a faith healer,

28:09.100 --> 28:11.700
born with
X-ray vision.

28:11.767 --> 28:15.333
She denied it for years,
said it embarrassed her.

28:15.400 --> 28:17.367
Then she goes
and heals a friend

28:17.433 --> 28:21.100
and the word spreads.

28:21.166 --> 28:26.467
All this time,
right next door to me.

28:26.533 --> 28:27.533
I was pissed off at first,
to tell you the truth.

28:27.600 --> 28:29.467
But she's the real deal.

28:29.533 --> 28:31.567
No showbiz shit.

28:31.633 --> 28:35.266
- But you still
limp a little.

28:35.333 --> 28:37.433
- Just started
bothering me again.

28:37.500 --> 28:39.834
But still, it's better
than what it used to be.

28:41.667 --> 28:45.633
God may hold the key
to your grandson's health,

28:45.700 --> 28:47.767
to heal him,

28:47.834 --> 28:51.333
but he's holding a key
inside the boy.

28:51.400 --> 28:52.900
Regina can turn it.

28:52.967 --> 28:54.934
- Absolutely not.

28:55.000 --> 28:56.600
- Sarah, listen to me.

28:56.667 --> 28:58.166
- I have listened to you.

28:58.233 --> 29:01.033
There will be no strange woman
doing some sort of séance

29:01.100 --> 29:04.300
or voodoo
over Alex Jr.'s bed.

29:04.367 --> 29:05.633
I will not
have it.

29:05.700 --> 29:07.533
- Put aside your prejudices
for a moment,

29:07.600 --> 29:09.333
take Mother
and go meet her.

29:09.400 --> 29:10.834
- No.

29:10.900 --> 29:13.066
There is no way I'm going
to dangle that kind of carrot

29:13.133 --> 29:16.133
in front of a terminally ill
10-year-old.

29:16.200 --> 29:17.800
The boy is
too fragile.

29:17.867 --> 29:20.033
Say it doesn't work,
Robert.

29:20.100 --> 29:21.400
What then?

29:21.467 --> 29:23.600
We tell him that God
didn't love him enough?

29:23.667 --> 29:26.133
- I don't want
little Alex to die.

29:26.200 --> 29:28.233
- We're waiting
and praying

29:28.300 --> 29:30.533
for a bone marrow
transplant.

29:30.600 --> 29:33.533
- Waiting and praying,
waiting and praying.

29:33.600 --> 29:35.967
What about doing,
God damn it?

29:36.033 --> 29:37.767
- Cool down, Rebadow.

29:37.834 --> 29:41.200
- Step back,
this is a family matter.

29:41.266 --> 29:44.667
I want to stand on a mountaintop
and curse our idiotic,

29:44.734 --> 29:48.000
modern small-mindedness,
our lame,

29:48.066 --> 29:50.333
civilized methods
of surviving sickness.

29:50.400 --> 29:53.200
Hospitals are the summit
of human potential?

29:53.266 --> 29:55.133
Bull-fucking-shit!

29:55.200 --> 29:56.300
- Are you finished?

29:56.367 --> 29:57.700
- No.

29:57.767 --> 29:59.633
I'll find someone else
to visit Regina for me.

29:59.700 --> 30:01.133
- Who?

30:01.200 --> 30:04.433
The only reason you called me
instead of Alex or Sophie

30:04.500 --> 30:06.900
or Mother is because you knew
that they would need convincing.

30:06.967 --> 30:09.400
No, there is no one
in our family

30:09.467 --> 30:12.600
who is going to let that strange
woman into Alex Jr.'s room.

30:12.667 --> 30:14.800
- You can't do this.

30:14.867 --> 30:16.200
- Yes, I can.

30:19.633 --> 30:20.734
You know what I see?

30:20.800 --> 30:22.200
I see a man trying
to redeem himself

30:22.266 --> 30:24.633
in the eyes
of his family,

30:24.700 --> 30:29.033
making a last-ditch effort
after decades of absence.

30:29.100 --> 30:30.133
See?

30:30.200 --> 30:33.367
Sometimes I have
X-ray vision too.

30:40.333 --> 30:41.667
- Why?

30:41.734 --> 30:44.600
Why open this door
just to close it in my face?

30:52.500 --> 30:54.000
Be healed...

30:57.066 --> 30:58.500
In the name of God.

31:01.266 --> 31:03.133
- Our Lady of Fatima Church
and its rectory next door

31:03.200 --> 31:04.900
were burned to the ground
this evening,

31:04.967 --> 31:06.500
killing two priests.

31:06.567 --> 31:08.800
